cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with sequence-to-sequence problems in natural language processing, specifically sentence summarization and machine translation. 
2. cs.LG (Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an end-to-end differentiable method for learning monotonic alignments. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural network models with an attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in AI. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with recurrent neural network models. 
5. cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper also deals with online speech recognition problems.
